Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.70,0:00:06.47,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I’m telling you! {Ad text at bottom}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.47,0:00:08.02,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,What? No way! {Ad text at bottom}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.91,0:00:12.97,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,M-Mary-chan! We heard!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.97,0:00:16.59,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You cleared your 50,000,000 debt and got out of being a Mike, right? {450,000 Usd}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.59,0:00:19.56,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,That’s so like you, Mary-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.14,0:00:19.56,Kakegurui - Up,,0,0,0,,You got that right!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.61,0:00:25.56,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,S-So, um... for everything up till now...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.96,0:00:28.04,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,We're sorry, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.65,0:00:39.18,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Come on! There’s nothing to worry about, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.18,0:00:41.20,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,We're friends, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.44,0:00:43.07,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Y-You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.07,0:00:45.57,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,My, what was I thinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.62,0:00:52.69,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Sure! Let's go out for some cake again some time!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.89,0:01:01.23,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,It’s nothing. Bullying livestock is \Nan academy rule, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.23,0:01:02.22,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,It was no wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.65,0:01:04.42,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.42,0:01:07.72,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Livestock becoming human again \Nalmost never happens, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.72,0:01:09.57,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,They were just too focused on that one exception
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.57,0:01:11.82,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,they could bully at their leisure and let it get to their heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.96,0:01:15.21,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Honestly, what a bunch of idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.21,0:01:17.32,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Well, leaving that aside...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.34,0:01:22.62,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I'll never forgive the Student Council \Nfor making a fool out of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.52,0:01:26.37,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,More importantly, about Yumeko...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.72,0:01:31.98,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Did you know? She really cashed in at the Debt Adjustment Assembly,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.98,0:01:33.51,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,but she still hasn’t paid back her debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.96,0:01:37.96,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,She already had the chance to lower her debt at the Assembly,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.96,0:01:40.01,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,but she’s willfully wasting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.01,0:01:42.81,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.84,0:01:46.51,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,She doesn't want to let go \Nof her Mike position.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.51,0:01:47.64,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I guess it’d more accurate to say
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.64,0:01:49.94,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,she wants to keep \Nthe benefits that come with being a Mike...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.51,0:01:53.19,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,How could being a Mike have benefits...?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.88,0:01:55.94,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,That's right. Official matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.20,0:02:00.86,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,No way! Is Yumeko planning to challenge \Nthe Student Council to an official match?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.86,0:02:04.38,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You. You haven’t heard anything about that from Yumeko?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.38,0:02:06.13,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Anything, meaning…?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.13,0:02:08.54,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,If she just wanted to gamble, she'd have ample opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.54,0:02:10.88,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,So why does it have to be an official game?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.88,0:02:13.34,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,No, I haven't heard anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.62,0:02:15.43,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.43,0:02:16.38,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.38,0:02:19.88,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I think she mentioned that she wanted to play against the Student Council President...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.88,0:02:21.01,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.01,0:02:22.72,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Suzui-san, Mary-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.33,0:02:24.60,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.96,0:02:26.82,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Morning, Yumeko.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.69,0:02:31.43,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Mary-san, I gave it some thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.43,0:02:36.32,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I don’t believe I could possibly accept \Nthe money we gained at that assembly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.69,0:02:37.78,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.78,0:02:41.83,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I already used 10,000,000 to pay off my debt anyway. {90,000 Usd}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.83,0:02:44.58,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,But that money is something we won by virtue of cooperation, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.99,0:02:48.58,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I don't want to owe you anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.00,0:02:51.67,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\pos(510,761.625)}Get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.58,0:02:51.67,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\pos(675,760.124)}Through.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.91,0:02:51.67,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\pos(828,761.625)}Your.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.41,0:02:51.67,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\pos(955.5,761.625)}Head!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.56,0:02:54.21,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,O-Of course..
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.21,0:02:56.00,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I suppose I'll take you up on that, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.30,0:02:59.02,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah. Just take it already!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.51,0:04:44.91,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Jabami Yumeko’s life plan forms won’t be withdrawn?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.08,0:04:47.24,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Yes. The President herself decided so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.47,0:04:49.08,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,And just what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.08,0:04:53.20,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,She should have won 260,000,000 from last week's assembly. {2,400,000 Usd}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.20,0:04:54.75,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Do we just forget about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.86,0:04:58.94,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I cannot say for certain what the President may be thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.94,0:05:03.34,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,However, I have conducted a background check on Jabami Yumeko by her orders,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.58,0:05:06.75,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,and have learned that she has quite the assets at her disposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.75,0:05:07.55,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.82,0:05:10.16,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Jabami Yumeko is living alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.16,0:05:14.71,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Her parents have passed and her only relative is an older sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.71,0:05:19.66,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,For a long time, her sister has been hospitalised in a university's special ward,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.66,0:05:22.86,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,and she has been taking responsibility for her treatment fees.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.00,0:05:26.94,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Having enormous assets is the only perceivable conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.83,0:05:33.54,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Does that mean that, should she feel no need \Nto pay back her debt, she simply won’t?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.09,0:05:35.87,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Just what could she be planning?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.87,0:05:38.50,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,NIha! That's super obvious, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.82,0:05:40.22,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,She wants an official match.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.22,0:05:42.86,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Yumeko wants to gamble with the Council President!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.37,0:05:45.13,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Woah, that surprised me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.87,0:05:49.16,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Midari-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.16,0:05:51.89,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Yumeko wants an official match with the President...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.84,0:05:54.18,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,That's bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.18,0:05:56.23,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,The president's gonna break her!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.39,0:05:57.52,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Not good!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.52,0:06:01.29,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Not good! Not good! Not good! Not good! Not good! Not good!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.29,0:06:02.99,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,She's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.55,0:06:02.90,Kakegurui - Up,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.99,0:06:04.22,Kakegurui - Up,,0,0,0,,Ikishima!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.78,0:06:07.32,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Just what's the matter with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.32,0:06:08.49,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Nyaha...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.78,0:06:12.54,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Better take care, Midari-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.49,0:06:20.67,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Classes are finally over!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.67,0:06:23.22,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I simply couldn't wait; my head was in the clouds!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.22,0:06:24.59,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Now, let us go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.84,0:06:28.39,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Um... You’re not talking about an official match, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.39,0:06:29.72,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.72,0:06:32.47,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Uh… wouldn't it be better if you prepared yourself a little more?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.47,0:06:35.59,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,My mental preparations have already been met, \Nso there is no issue on that front!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.59,0:06:38.35,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,No, that's not what I meant...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.78,0:06:42.01,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wanting to challenge the President that made her lose again...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.01,0:06:45.32,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What’s driving Yumeko to do this?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.37,0:06:51.92,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,All right. You should be able to issue \Na challenge in the Student Council Room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.92,0:06:52.96,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I'll show you the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.96,0:06:54.53,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.25,0:07:01.66,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}An official match with the Student Council President, huh?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.66,0:07:04.63,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Well, that 250,000,000 was just easy money anyways,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.63,0:07:06.89,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}so I don't care what she does now but...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.89,0:07:09.80,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Mary-chan, wanna go back together?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.76,0:07:12.68,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What should I do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.96,0:07:17.02,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've both lost and won in the web of their plots...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.64,0:07:25.98,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just thinking that they're playing me makes the blood rush to my head, it makes me sick...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.91,0:07:29.74,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is it fine to keep on like this?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.54,0:07:46.32,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Saotome Mary-san, would you mind joining me for tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.32,0:07:47.67,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Just the two of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.19,0:07:53.13,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I found you, Yumeko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.45,0:07:55.60,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You are… the one from before!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.60,0:07:58.39,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your assistance back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.91,0:08:05.18,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Yumeko. I hear you still haven't paid \Nback that 310,000,000 debt, right? {2,800,000 Usd}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.18,0:08:08.07,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,As the head of the beautification committee, I can't let that slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.11,0:08:12.33,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,What are you doing \Nso out of the blue?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.45,0:08:17.62,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Correcting the garbage around school to make sure it becomes beautiful again...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.62,0:08:20.29,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,That's the duty of \Nthe beautification committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.57,0:08:24.37,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I'm also one of the few with the right to arrest students.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.57,0:08:24.29,Kakegurui - Overlap,,0,0,0,,Wai–
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.64,0:08:25.69,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Take her away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.69,0:08:26.78,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Okay~
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.15,0:08:31.67,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I do have to investigate her, after all. Thoroughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.67,0:08:34.62,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,No, wait! You can't just arrest–
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.80,0:08:34.62,Kakegurui - Up,,0,0,0,,While you're at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.62,0:08:36.01,Kakegurui - Up,,0,0,0,,Take this guy with you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.89,0:08:37.18,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Okay~
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.26,0:08:52.40,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Don't make that face, Yumeko.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.60,0:08:53.35,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.35,0:08:55.31,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Whatever could you want from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.31,0:08:56.95,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I have plans for later, I’ll have you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.12,0:08:59.99,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Plans, huh? I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.45,0:09:05.69,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Do you think a delinquent like you \Ncould even meet the Council President, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.69,0:09:08.84,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,An official match is even more out of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.84,0:09:10.92,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,But hey, if you insist...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.09,0:09:14.72,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,If you keep insisting on getting it on with the President…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:18.26,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,then you'll need to gamble with me first, Yumeko.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.41,0:09:19.89,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Oh my! Gamble?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.16,0:09:23.24,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,If that’s the case, I do wish you \Nwould have mentioned so sooner!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.24,0:09:25.22,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Well, what will we play?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.86,0:09:30.11,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I thought you’d say something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.11,0:09:31.90,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I get it, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.90,0:09:33.82,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You and I are the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.50,0:09:36.88,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,We’re both perverts that get off on thrills!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.88,0:09:40.55,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Oh my. Calling me a pervert is rather crude!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.94,0:09:44.25,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Now then,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.25,0:09:48.17,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,this is an underground investigation facility that was built specifically
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.17,0:09:49.88,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,to deal with the trash of this academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.15,0:09:52.86,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,There’s a hearing room for directly questioning people...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.86,0:09:56.74,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,and a separate observation room \Nwhere you can keep an eye on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.24,0:09:59.76,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Both rooms are completely soundproof
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.76,0:10:04.39,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,and the only thing connecting them are the cameras and monitors installed in both rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.17,0:10:08.20,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,We call this the ‘Esp Game’.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.20,0:10:09.60,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,The rules are simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.60,0:10:11.31,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,It's a card-matching game where
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.31,0:10:14.40,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,all we have to do is guess the cards the dealer in the other room lays down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.02,0:10:17.11,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,To explain the game with more detail:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.11,0:10:19.78,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,First, the dealer can place the cards in any order they like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.57,0:10:24.38,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,We can see the dealer’s movements through the monitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.38,0:10:28.11,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Once the dealer’s done, it's our turn to line up the cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.11,0:10:30.29,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Once that’s done, all three of us show our cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.71,0:10:34.70,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,The one with more cards in their \Nline-up that match the dealer’s wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.70,0:10:36.92,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Each matching card is worth one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.06,0:10:39.69,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I see, it's nice and simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.69,0:10:40.97,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,How much do we bet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.50,0:10:44.72,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Hey Yumeko, you’re being rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.72,0:10:47.04,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Don't fuck around.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.04,0:10:51.23,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,We're not gonna bet on something as simple as money.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.23,0:10:52.69,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,The winner of the game
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.69,0:10:55.92,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,gets to pull the trigger once for every point they have over the other!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.92,0:10:59.36,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,We'll load the gun with as many bullets \Nas we want and spin the chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.80,0:11:02.68,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,The highest you can go is six bullets!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.68,0:11:06.20,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You can load all of them, but loading none's just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.60,0:11:11.78,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,After that, we send them down that chute so that we don’t know the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.78,0:11:14.59,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,The winner gets to take one of the guns and pull the trigger,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.59,0:11:17.92,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,but only for every point that goes over the opponent's.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.52,0:11:21.97,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,It's a loss decided by getting hit just once!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.60,0:11:26.26,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,What do you say? Pretty interesting, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.26,0:11:29.18,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but that can’t be anything other than an air gun, ri–
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.60,0:11:39.94,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,If you get it we’ll start, Yumeko.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.33,0:11:42.80,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You're the only one I can rely on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.80,0:11:45.99,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Let’s have the best read-and-kill game, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.25,0:11:50.65,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Don’t worry, it's not like you'd just drop dead from just one hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.65,0:11:53.50,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,We’ll take you to the hospital real quick, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.77,0:11:58.81,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Oh. Are you worried about what happens if you kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.81,0:12:01.12,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Moron! It's all good!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.12,0:12:03.55,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,The President’s gonna do something \Nabout whatever happens then!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.82,0:12:07.93,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,A shooting incident at school would \Nmake its reputation take a nosedive!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.47,0:12:11.43,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you, she'll definitely do everything to keep it a secret from society!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.73,0:12:14.42,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You don't need to worry about anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.42,0:12:18.78,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Let's enjoy ourselves to our heart's content!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.00,0:12:22.05,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Does she have a few screws loose?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.05,0:12:25.28,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Let's go back, Yumeko. We don't have any reason to play along with someone like–
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.98,0:12:29.72,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Listen, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.72,0:12:32.75,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Why are you getting in the way of our fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.61,0:12:37.45,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Even the Council President won't \Ntake me on. Yumeko's all I've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.45,0:12:38.25,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.88,0:12:42.08,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I'm begging you. Just let me do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.08,0:12:44.34,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I just... I can't hold it in anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.34,0:12:47.60,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,It's making me go crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.60,0:12:48.73,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Stop fooling around!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.73,0:12:50.04,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Just let us out of here already!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.28,0:12:52.00,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Why, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.00,0:12:55.04,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Can't you see how much I'm begging?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.04,0:12:59.07,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,A gamble this insane... there's no way \NIn Hell we'd play, begging or no!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.88,0:13:02.26,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.66,0:13:04.54,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I get it already...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.02,0:13:08.07,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You. You're in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.33,0:13:11.33,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Come now, do calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:16.16,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I haven't said anything about not playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.16,0:13:17.33,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Yu-Yumeko...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.68,0:13:21.09,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I can't say I'm too fond of gambles this pragmatic,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.55,0:13:23.84,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,but since you've gone this far I see no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.84,0:13:25.15,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I will accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.15,0:13:27.13,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,W-What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.13,0:13:30.16,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,A gamble like this is just... too...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.97,0:13:34.38,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You're kidding, right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.38,0:13:37.52,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1000)\i1}That makes you seem like...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.90,0:13:41.02,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The same kind of person!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.84,0:13:46.28,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,This is Ceylon Dimbula tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.28,0:13:48.29,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,It has a rather florid scent, wouldn't you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.29,0:13:50.99,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I do hope it suits your taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.97,0:13:55.87,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You've certainly made me enjoy the Assembly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.48,0:14:01.09,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You were the first to actually garner hundreds of millions from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.84,0:14:05.17,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Most don't notice the loophole in \Nthe rules of the Debt Exchange.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.53,0:14:09.78,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,And when they do, they mostly stick to small, minute earnings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.78,0:14:11.67,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,How boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.67,0:14:14.52,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You've managed to move beyond \Nyour debt and Mike status, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.36,0:14:19.94,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Now I have no choice left but \Nto tear up your life plan form.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.64,0:14:22.75,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,What a loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.24,0:14:27.29,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,J-Just what are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.29,0:14:30.00,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,That was just some arbitrary rule you decided to push on me–
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.00,0:14:32.49,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Well, I can't say that it matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.37,0:14:34.99,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Mary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.22,0:14:39.21,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\pos(523.5,761.625)}Join
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.72,0:14:39.21,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\pos(787.5,761.625)}the Student Council.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.61,0:14:40.23,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.46,0:14:44.66,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Before accepting this gamble, \NI have three conditions that should be met.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.66,0:14:47.40,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,We only play three rounds in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.40,0:14:49.78,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Suzui-san will be playing the dealer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.78,0:14:50.20,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.38,0:14:54.26,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,And... the losing side must pay a total of 1,000,000,000 Yen. {Approximately 9,000,000 Usd}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.52,0:14:59.96,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Do you even get your situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.96,0:15:02.76,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Why are {\i1}you{\i0} setting conditions here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.82,0:15:05.53,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You're fucking insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.36,0:15:09.93,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.93,0:15:11.85,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,1,000,000,000, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.85,0:15:16.22,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,That's fine. I couldn't care less about money, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.22,0:15:20.24,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,And I don't care if this... Suzui? \Nwhatever his name is plays the dealer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.24,0:15:22.54,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You probably think that I'd cheat, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.97,0:15:24.73,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.73,0:15:27.30,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,The fuck is this about three rounds?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.73,0:15:30.80,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You're not trying for a fucking draw, are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.32,0:15:35.00,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,"As long as I win at the card line-up \Nand miss on purpose it'll be fine."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.00,0:15:37.33,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You're not thinking about shit like that, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.33,0:15:38.81,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Who knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.29,0:15:45.69,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Fine! With guts like yours, there's no way \Nyou'd make a game boring, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.69,0:15:47.89,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I believe in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.89,0:15:49.78,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,But I'll need some insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.20,0:15:52.36,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I'm adding a rule!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.36,0:15:55.70,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,If someone misses a shot, the other gets to shoot instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.70,0:15:57.49,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Then I won't mind having three rounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.93,0:16:00.48,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Of course, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.72,0:16:02.39,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Great! Let's get this started!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.62,0:16:03.66,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,That's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.66,0:16:07.38,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Even if you get the right cards, \Nyou still can't miss on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.38,0:16:09.76,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,It's guaranteed that one of them gets shot–
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.93,0:16:13.60,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Suzui! Get to the observation room already!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.76,0:16:17.85,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Having Suzui-san as the dealer is rather reassuring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.85,0:16:20.16,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No... you're overestimating me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.16,0:16:23.56,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yumeko's life depends on the way I set up my cards...!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.33,0:16:37.53,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Suzui-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.05,0:16:39.54,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.54,0:16:43.49,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,The two of us have 'that' after all, don't we? 'That'...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.49,0:16:44.59,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.59,0:16:46.79,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,If we use 'that' as a sign, we'll definitely win.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.84,0:16:49.34,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,That's the spirit, Yumeko!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.69,0:16:53.06,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Well then, Suzui-san. I will see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.22,0:16:58.64,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,A sign?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.64,0:17:02.38,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You really think he can tell you \Nthe right cards with just his hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.38,0:17:03.98,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You need to be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.61,0:17:07.20,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Here you go, these are the Esp cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.20,0:17:10.48,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You lay them down on the desk's black field \Nso that the camera can see them...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.90,0:17:14.76,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,And showing anything other than \Nthe cards and your hands is a no-go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.53,0:17:19.65,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\u0\i1}The one thing I have to watch out \Nthe most for in this game is cheating.{\u0\i1}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.65,0:17:22.37,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In other words, having Ikishima know the order of my cards.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.88,0:17:26.50,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Right now, there's nothing that warrants that suspicion.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:30.60,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All that's left is figuring out how to line these cards up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.60,0:17:31.92,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The problem is...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.44,0:17:35.05,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If we use 'that' as a sign, \Nwe'll definitely win.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.40,0:17:36.57,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If we use 'that' as a sign...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.57,0:17:38.08,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If we use 'that' as a sign...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.08,0:17:39.28,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i0}If we use 'that' as a sign...{\i1}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.46,0:17:44.25,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\pos(633.858,761.625)\i1}Just what...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.46,0:17:44.25,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\u0\i1\pos(860.572,761.625)}is 'that'?!{\u1\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.00,0:17:46.35,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Please spare me your jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.05,0:17:48.60,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Why should I join the Council?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.60,0:17:51.04,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm completely serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.04,0:17:56.74,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,That ability, that talent of yours... it earned you \N310,000,000 Yen from the Student Council.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.13,0:18:02.04,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I'm saying that you're just the right fit for the Student Council.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.76,0:18:04.29,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,There's no way...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.29,0:18:09.64,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,In other words... you're declining the \Nrequest of the Student Council President?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.70,0:18:13.32,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,And just why, I wonder?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.32,0:18:18.88,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You should understand the profits of being \Na Council member more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.42,0:18:20.64,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,So, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.61,0:18:23.85,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Do the other members frighten you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.85,0:18:26.93,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Then why would you even make the \Ncouncil suffer such an enormous loss?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.69,0:18:30.10,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Do you doubt me, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.10,0:18:31.94,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Then you can just put the position on hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.48,0:18:36.03,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,There's no way you could just reject it without hesitation, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.90,0:18:38.63,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Well? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.46,0:18:41.39,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I'm listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.12,0:18:48.41,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Oh, I apologise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.41,0:18:52.17,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,It's just that I can't understand your actions, not one bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.65,0:18:57.92,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\pos(571.5,761.625)}People like you that I can't comprehend...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.59,0:18:57.92,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1141.5,761.625)}I love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.90,0:19:03.29,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Suzui, get on with it already!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.29,0:19:05.80,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Thinking won't get you anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.80,0:19:07.76,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She may be right.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.76,0:19:09.02,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's no way
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.02,0:19:12.36,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}someone who only just got out of being livestock could shoulder this kind of task...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.70,0:19:16.52,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It wasn't even my own power that got me out of being livestock.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.52,0:19:17.90,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was thanks to Yumeko.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.09,0:19:22.86,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Of course. That's exactly why I have to be the one to do it!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.86,0:19:26.62,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yumeko's saved me before. Now it's my turn!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.24,0:19:30.53,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Think this through. What can I do to help Yumeko?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.53,0:19:33.48,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Think! As if you could die!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.54,0:19:38.01,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Ah. Looks like he's done with preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.77,0:19:44.38,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yumeko's objective is to definitely win \Nby using a 'sign' we both know.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.38,0:19:45.93,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At least, that's what \Nshe wants Ikishima to think.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.70,0:19:49.62,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's no way she'd load her gun in a match she can't win.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.62,0:19:54.08,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So Ikishima can't load her gun \Nuntil she sees through that 'sign'!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.08,0:19:57.73,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I'm reading the situation right, \Nthe sign can be anything.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.73,0:20:00.44,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sending any kind of sign is vital!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.74,0:20:05.46,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Two? Or are those supposed to be scissors?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.46,0:20:08.33,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Just what could that mean, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.33,0:20:12.31,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Does this screen show the room \Nsuzui-san's in at the moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.31,0:20:17.84,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Yeah. You can't hear his voice, but unlike with \Nhim our hands aren't the only thing being taped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.12,0:20:24.60,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I see. I do believe I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.60,0:20:26.80,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Good. First, load the gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.46,0:20:38.13,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Yumeko, you don't need to tell me how many bullets you loaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.13,0:20:40.86,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Still, I should probably tell you something...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.52,0:20:45.03,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I'm loading six!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.18,0:20:47.16,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.54,0:20:51.80,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}J-Just now... Ikishima definitely \Nloaded six bullets, didn't she?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.80,0:20:53.24,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}T-That's ridiculous!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.24,0:20:55.93,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If we did have a sign, that'd be suicidal!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.93,0:20:58.79,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No way... did she find out the 'sign' was a bluff?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.61,0:21:05.66,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Finally! A card line-up that risks our {\i1}lives!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.84,0:21:07.41,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You're ready, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.41,0:21:08.53,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.18,0:21:20.74,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Okay. Make him show his cards.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.74,0:21:21.94,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Okay~
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.94,0:21:24.20,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Suzui! Show the cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.04,0:21:28.05,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All I can do is pray...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.05,0:21:28.70,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.76,0:21:34.50,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I can't get enough of this moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.50,0:21:36.22,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Okay. Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.22,0:21:37.08,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I'm flipping them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.30,0:21:53.75,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Ikishima, three cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.99,0:21:56.77,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Yumeko... two cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.19,0:21:59.75,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Yumeko... lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.13,0:22:02.30,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.30,0:22:04.58,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Was that sign a bluff?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.58,0:22:06.16,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Well, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.16,0:22:09.30,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,You said you were ready, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.82,0:22:12.81,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Hey, Yumeko...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.81,0:22:16.27,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Don't make it hard to look at you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.44,0:22:24.67,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Ikishima-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.27,0:22:27.93,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,I don't recommend that you pull that gun's trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.53,0:22:28.92,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.70,0:24:09.70,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.70,0:24:11.89,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,No one's seen the dark side of the moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.96,0:24:12.22,Kakegurui - Up,,0,0,0,,Is that the trick?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.89,0:24:14.52,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Please keep your ridicule in moderation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.98,0:24:17.38,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Someday, I'll do you a favour and kill you...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.66,0:24:17.38,Kakegurui - Up,,0,0,0,,Council President!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.58,0:24:21.00,Kakegurui,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
